13 by striking out the following: "the State's"
14 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 2nd line (page 1, line 18 in L.D.)
15 by striking out the following: "telecommunications" and inserting the following:
16 'communications'
17 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-A in the 2nd line (page 1, line 18 in L.D.)
18 by striking out the following: "services or critical" and inserting the following: 'services
19 affecting the State or the State's critical'
20 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 8 in the 2nd and 3rd lines (page 1, lines 25
21 and 26 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "in furtherance of political or social
22 objectives"
23 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 8 in the 6th line (page 1, line 29 in L.D.) by
24 striking out the following: "physical" and inserting the following: 'physical'
25 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 8 in the 7th line (page 1, line 30 in L.D.) by
26 striking out the following: "the State's"
27 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 8 in the 7th line (page 1, line 30 in L.D.) by
28 striking out the following: "telecommunications" and inserting the following:
29 'communications'
30 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 8 in the 8th line (page 1, line 31 in L.D.) by
31 striking out the following: "services or critical" and inserting the following: 'services
32 affecting the State or the State's critical'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR0492(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 147, L.D. 224
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, changes references to
33 cyberattacks targeting state technology infrastructure, systems, services and critical
44 infrastructure to more broadly include such attacks that affect the State. It also removes
55 the requirement for a cyberattack to be in furtherance of political or social objectives to be
66 considered terrorism and makes other technical changes.
Page 2 - 132LR0492(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
